      "id": "65e8359f7e405b05c70e04fe",
      "uuid": "498f3fc9-46f7-44d0-9969-02f582cc88f8",
      "title": "10 common errors encountered when trading VNST",
      "slug": "10-common-errors-encountered-when-trading-vnst",
      "html": "<figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2024/03/10-l-i-th--ng-g-p_ENG-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1011\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2024/03/10-l-i-th--ng-g-p_ENG-1.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2024/03/10-l-i-th--ng-g-p_ENG-1.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1600/2024/03/10-l-i-th--ng-g-p_ENG-1.png 1600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2024/03/10-l-i-th--ng-g-p_ENG-1.png 1800w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p><em>During the use and transaction of VNST, users may encounter common errors. Here are 10 common errors when trading VNST and how to fix them.</em></p><h3 id=\"1-sorry-you-have-no-permission-to-access-this-function-please-try-again-later\">1. Sorry, you have no permission to access this function. Please try again later.</h3><p>When encountering the authentication error on the Wallet, refusing authentication can significantly hinder the user's transaction process. In this case, accepting the authentication request on the Wallet is necessary to continue the transaction smoothly and securely. This not only protects the user's personal information and assets but also ensures the integrity of the VNST transaction process.</p><h3 id=\"2-the-mint-covered-price-is-being-updated-please-wait-a-few-minutes-before-you-try-again-or-contact-us-here\">2. The Mint Covered Price is being updated. Please wait a few minutes before you try again, or contact us here.</h3><p>In the situation where the market price is lower than the support price during minting, it indicates a system error that may occur due to inaccurate price setting. In this case, the transaction will be temporarily suspended until the error is rectified and the system returns to normal operation.</p><h3 id=\"3-the-redeem-covered-price-is-being-updated-please-wait-a-few-minutes-before-you-try-again-or-contact-us-here\">3. The Redeem Covered Price is being updated. Please wait a few minutes before you try again, or contact us here.</h3><p>Similar to minting VNST, when encountering a situation where the market price is lower than the support price during redemption, it is usually a sign of a system error, possibly originating from inaccurate price setting. In this case, the transaction process will be temporarily suspended until the error is resolved, and the system returns to normal operation.</p><h3 id=\"4-insufficient-balance-please-deposit-more\">4. Insufficient balance, please deposit more!</h3><p>This often happens when users input a quantity of VNST (or USDT) exceeding the available balance in their account. Users will not be able to conduct transactions until they input the correct available VNST (or USDT) balance in their account.</p><h3 id=\"5-min-5-usdt\">5. Min: 5 USDT</h3><p>In this case, transactions cannot be conducted if the quantity is less than 5 USDT. To resolve this issue, users need to input a quantity equal to or greater than 5 USDT to continue the transaction process smoothly and efficiently.</p><h3 id=\"6-max-199999-usdt\">6. Max: 1,999.99 USDT</h3><p>When users input a quantity greater than 1,999.99 USDT, the system will not be able to conduct transactions as it exceeds the specified limit. Users are only allowed to input a quantity equal to or less than 1,999.99 USDT to continue the transaction process effectively.</p><h3 id=\"7-mint-covered-amount-is-temporarily-unavailable-please-wait-a-few-minutes\">7. Mint covered amount is temporarily unavailable, please wait a few minutes!</h3><p>In the case where the mint support volume is unavailable, it often occurs when the Operating Pool has supported all VNST during minting. At that time, users will temporarily be unable to receive VNST support when conducting mint transactions. However, users can wait and handle this error after the Operating Pool adds VNST, to continue the transaction process as usual.</p><h3 id=\"8-redeem-covered-amount-is-temporarily-unavailable-please-wait-a-few-minutes\">8. Redeem covered amount is temporarily unavailable, please wait a few minutes!</h3><p>When the redeem support volume is unavailable, it typically occurs when the Operating Pool has supported all USDT during redemption. In this situation, users will temporarily be unable to receive VNST support when conducting redemption transactions. However, they can wait and handle this error after the Operating Pool adds VNST, to continue the transaction process as usual.</p><h3 id=\"9-reminder-please-connect-to-the-appropriate-network\">9. Reminder Please connect to the appropriate network</h3><p>The notification \"Reminder Please connect to the appropriate network\" often appears when users use an incorrect Blockchain network for their transactions. To resolve this issue, users need to choose the appropriate Blockchain network for their assets and transaction types to ensure the success and safety of the transaction process.</p><h3 id=\"10-erc20-insufficient-allowance\">10. ERC20: Insufficient allowance!</h3><p>This often occurs when users do not accept Wallet authentication. Transactions cannot continue without authentication from the user. To overcome this issue, users need to accept Wallet authentication to continue and complete transactions successfully and safely.</p><p>In the above article, we have compiled common errors when trading VNST and how to fix them. Understanding and applying error correction measures is crucial to ensure a smooth and secure transaction process<em>. </em>Don't forget to follow our channels to stay updated with the latest information from the event!</p><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/vnstcoin?ref=blog.vnst.io\">X</a> | <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/VNST.io/\">Facebook </a>| <a href=\"https://t.me/vnstann?ref=blog.vnst.io\">Telegram Announcements</a> |  <a href=\"https://discord.gg/pwRwbcHHkK?ref=blog.vnst.io\">Discord</a></p>",
