      "html": "<blockquote>VNST is a separate payment and transaction confirmation system on-chain 24/7, meeting the needs of using and converting VNST at market exchange rates. In this article, we will detail the steps to use VNST's Mint &amp; Redeem feature.</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/mint-redeem-Done--1--1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/mint-redeem-Done--1--1.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/mint-redeem-Done--1--1.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/mint-redeem-Done--1--1.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><h3 id=\"mint-vnst-from-usdt\"><strong>Mint VNST from USDT</strong></h3><p>Step 1: Connect wallet </p><blockquote>VNST currently supports Metamask, Coinbase Wallet, Binance Wallet, Coin98 Wallet, Wallet Connect, Trust Wallet</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-7.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1354\" height=\"638\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-7.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-7.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-7.png 1354w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Step 2: Go to Mint &amp; Redeem page: https://vnst.io/en/mint-and-redeem and choose Mint.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-8.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1357\" height=\"639\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-8.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-8.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-8.png 1357w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Step 3: Enter the amount of USDT you want to Mint to VNST </p><blockquote>*Note: The Beta version of the VNST.io website has not yet integrated the KYC feature, so to comply with AML and CTF, Smart Contract will limit all orders below 2000$ </blockquote><blockquote>Exchange rates will be updated every 5 minutes, ensuring users always get Mint with the best exchange rate</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-9.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1360\" height=\"643\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-9.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-9.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-9.png 1360w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Step 4: Sign the transaction at your wallet and receive VNST</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-20.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1366\" height=\"644\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-20.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-20.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-20.png 1366w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><h2 id=\"redeem-usdt-from-vnst\">Redeem USDT from VNST</h2><p>Step 1: Connect wallet </p><blockquote>VNST currently supports Metamask, Coinbase Wallet, Binance Wallet, Coin98 Wallet, Wallet Connect, Trust Wallet</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-11.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1364\" height=\"636\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-11.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-11.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-11.png 1364w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Step 2: Go to Mint &amp; Redeem page: https://vnst.io/en/mint-and-redeem . Then, select Redeem</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-12.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1362\" height=\"641\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-12.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-12.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-12.png 1362w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Step 3: Enter the amount of VNST you want to redeem </p><blockquote>Note: the Beta version of the VNST.io website has not yet integrated the KYC feature, so to comply with AML and CTF, Smart Contract will limit all orders below 2000$ </blockquote><blockquote>Redeem fees will be 0.1% per transaction</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-19.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1366\" height=\"639\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-19.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-19.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-19.png 1366w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Step 4: Sign the transaction at your wallet and receive USDT</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-18.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1358\" height=\"641\" srcset=\"https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w600/2023/09/image-18.png 600w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/size/w1000/2023/09/image-18.png 1000w, https://blog.vnst.io/content/images/2023/09/image-18.png 1358w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 720px) 720px\"></figure><p>Above are detailed instructions on how to use the Mint &amp; Redeem feature at the website VNST.io.</p><h2 id=\"about-vnst\">About VNST</h2><p>VNST is a decentralized stablecoin with transparent on-chain data, guaranteed by the stable value of the most popular and reputable stable coins in the global crypto asset market. The stablecoins that ensure value for VNST have transaction volume and stability proven over a long period of time, issued by reputable organizations with proven potential and periodically audited. VNST will be a safe, reliable solution, providing diverse and convenient choices and expanding future applications for users in the Web3 field in Vietnam and around the world.</p><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/vnstcoin?ref=blog.vnst.io\">X</a> | <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/VNST.io/\">Facebook </a>| <a href=\"https://t.me/vnstann?ref=blog.vnst.io\">Telegram Announcements</a> |  <a href=\"https://discord.gg/pwRwbcHHkK?ref=blog.vnst.io\">Discord</a> | <a href=\"https://t.me/vnstgroup?ref=blog.vnst.io\">Telegram Discussion</a></p>",
